## US-164: Wire offlineGrowth to chunk-based world

### Files Changed

**`game/stores/core.ts`** — Added `lastSavedAt: 0` to `initialState`. Persisted automatically via Legend State `syncObservable` so elapsed time can be calculated on every app resume.

**`game/hooks/useAutoSave.ts`** — Records `lastSavedAt = Date.now()` in `performSave()` before each save. Uses a module-level `isTimestampUpdate` flag to prevent the Legend State subscription from scheduling a cascade save — Legend State notifies observers synchronously during `.set()`, so the flag is visible when the subscriber fires.

**`game/systems/offlineGrowth.ts`** (133→206 lines) — Key additions:
- `calculateOfflineGrowth` now accepts optional `seasonMultiplier` and `weatherMultiplier` params (default 1.0, backward-compatible)
- New `ChunkGrowthSummary` interface reports `chunksUpdated`, `treesUpdated`, `stageAdvances`, `elapsedSeconds`
- New `applyOfflineGrowthToChunkDeltas(lastSavedAt, season, weatherType?, lookupSpecies?)` — reads all chunk diffs from `chunkDiffs$`, applies growth using season multipliers from `growth.json` and weather multipliers from `weather.json`, writes only changed diffs back via `saveChunkDiff`. Winter (multiplier=0) short-circuits before iterating.

**`game/systems/offlineGrowth.test.ts`** — Expanded from 12 to 33 tests, all passing ✓

